Counterpoint: This is the point of a bad sci fi movie. None of this is interesting to anyone except as a subject of discussion for a potential "dystopian future", the exact demographic for this sort of stuff is the same one that buys 80s type blowup dolls. None of it is happening

It's like saying AI is going to create perfect ads that make you buy stuff. This is the type of thing a marketing guy tells a company manager to scam him into buying his AI voodoo product. The only reason to believe it is if you're trying to make a profit off sensationalism
My good taste

Basically every time people try to describe "hellish Dystopian AI future world" they just reinvent television. Millennials were liberated from Old Media monotony and fell into horror at the Internet's vastness both craving and fearing a return to their primordial childhood's TV.

Everything they can name as a Matrix type tool of slavery is basically just an aspect of TV, VR goggles as sitting on couch staring instead of smartphone's mobility, "infinitely convincing AI" trope as a TV ad, censorship and control as just watching the program, it's all just TV

Smartphones are the same shape as old booklets due to carcinization. It's an effective form. No one will ever use computer glasses or whatever. Delusional fearmongering just distracts from contemporary real issues of using real technology properly or improperly. Mental ergonomics

I think it's essential to understand that a ZOGworld Dystopian future is not actually coming. Current available technology like twitter or smartphones is more advanced than any "VR goggles AI porn chatbot metaverse" sci-fi horror scenario delusions. None of it will ever happen.
